Councils were last night accused by ministers of ‘bending the law’ with their use of CCTV and overzealous parking wardens to catch out motorists and ‘fill their coffers’.

Eric Pickles fired a broadside after a parking watchdog told MPs that councils are ignoring official guidance on enforcement.

It said that, counter to the guidance, town halls are using surveillance cameras – which automatically issue fines – as a matter of ‘routine’, and leave no room for discretion.

